<footer class="footer">
  <div class="footer-col"><b>XORcel</b> is a browser-based tool for XOR-transforming integer columns in CSV files. XOR (exclusive or) is a reversible bitwise operation — applying the same key twice restores the original data. Use Transform to process files, and Explore to learn how it works.</div>
  <div class="footer-col"><b>Privacy.</b> All processing happens entirely in your browser. No data is uploaded, stored, or sent to any server. Your files never leave your machine.</div>
  <div class="footer-col"><b>Not encryption.</b> XOR encoding is a simple obfuscation technique, not a secure encryption method. The key can be recovered through frequency analysis or known-plaintext attacks. Do not use XORcel to protect sensitive, confidential, or regulated data. For real encryption, use AES or a similar standard.</div>
  <div class="footer-col"><b>Open source.</b> XORcel is free and open source. <a href="https://github.com/polyym/xorcel-webapp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:var(--indigo);text-decoration:underline;">View the source on GitHub</a>.</div>
</footer>
